November 24, 2009 is 'Ben Olsen Day' by order of the Mayor of DC.
Proclamation from Mayor Fenty for Ben Olsen...
Ben Olsen: "I enjoyed the game more as I got older. I slowed down and wasn't as streaky."
Ben Olsen: "I would not like to be considering for the head coaching job. I am in no way ready for that role."
Ben Olsen: "To sum my career up, I was a product of the environment - great coaches, great players and a great organization."
Ben Olsen: "Bruce made my career - he taught me how to play. I'm very grateful."
Ben Olsen: "One of the best decisions I ever made was going down to UVA and meeting Bruce Areana... he'll tell you that."
Ben Olsen: "the only person who is the heart and soul of this team is Kevin Payne."
Ben Olsen: "Jaime - he gets his own list [of the best players]. He will forever in this League."
Ben Olsen: "Of all the players in the history of the MLS, I've played with the best players - there's no question."
Ben Olsen: "The one thing I know I'll miss is the crowd and the support they give me... The Heart of the Lion banner - I still get chills."
Ben Olsen: "I can't believe this was my career. I was lucky. There weren't many things I didn't get to experience."
Ben Olsen: "I'm so lucky. I can't believe that I've been through this stuff."
Ben Olsen: "The more I think about it, it's a feeling of relief - not having to deal with the pain for another year."
Kevin Payne: "We should not let this pass without remarking on his contribution to the community, too."
Kevin Payne: "There have been many, many great players at D.C. United.. but, I don't know if any of them has made a greater impact"
Kevin Payne: "This is a bittersweet day for all us."
